snippet.textDisplay:
He's good but he has to work on just a few things:
1. He's pitchy in most performances. It's sometimes to an extreme level but it's something that he is probably working on right now.
2. His vibrato/instability often comes from moving his jaw quickly and excessively. This just isn't good technique and he should probably fix that.
3. He strains on "(and) IIIIII (tend to close my eyes when it hurts sometimes I fall into your) ARMS." His throat almost seems to lock up when he sings it live. This didn't happen at all in this performance but it usually does.
4. His hair xD JKJK
But his tone and emotion are always so good. I love this song with all of my heart.
